Houssem Aouar, 22, has been on Lyon’s books since 2009. And since breaking into the first-team ranks of the Ligue 1 giants for the first time at the beginning of 2017, the Lyon native has gone on to establish himself as one of the most highly-regarded talents in French football. All told, the youngster has notched 143 appearances across all competitions for Lyon, chipping in with 26 goals and 28 assists along the way. Such impressive displays have seen a host of Europe’s top outfits, including Manchester City, Juventus and Arsenal, linked with the midfielder. The latter of this trio looked to be the most interested party throughout the latest transfer window. But in the end, Arsenal would opt to sign a different midfielder, in the form of Thomas Partey. <img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Picture2-1-1024x699.jpg?resize=1024%2C699&#038;ssl=1" alt="MANCHESTER, ENGLAND - OCTOBER 17: Mikel Arteta, Manager of Arsenal talks to Thomas Partey of Arsenal before making his debut during the Premier League match between Manchester City and Arsenal at Etihad Stadium on October 17, 2020 in Manchester, England. Sporting stadiums around the UK remain under strict restrictions due to the Coronavirus Pandemic as Government social distancing laws prohibit fans inside venues resulting in games being played behind closed doors. (Photo by Michael Regan/Getty Images)" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-src="https://i1.wp.com/www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Picture2-1-1024x699.jpg?resize=1024%2C699&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" class=" jetpack-lazy-image"><img data-lazyloaded="1" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=" data-src="https://i1.wp.com/www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Picture2-1-1024x699.jpg?resize=1024%2C699&#038;ssl=1" alt="MANCHESTER, ENGLAND - OCTOBER 17: Mikel Arteta, Manager of 