sted in Aouar. According to a report from the Daily Mail, citing Italian outlet Tuttosport, the Gunners are still interested in trying to acquire the services of Aouar. However, they will face stiff competition from Juventus. The midfielder himself has also recently commented on him not leaving Lyon over the summer, but he insisted he is happy with the French outfit. “I am happy, this is my city and this my club. “I am proud to represent this club, I have so much motivation to make a great season. “We made a choice, I’m happy to stay here. Aulas and Juninho convinced me to stay in Lyon.” See also: Burnley vs Tottenham Hotspur betting tips: Premier League preview, predictions & odds Burnley vs Tottenham Hotspur live streaming: Watch Premier League online, preview, prediction and odds Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world. The latest word stemming from the French media suggests that Manchester City’s hopes of landing Lyon star Houssem Aouar may be dealt a blow by the club’s ban from European competition. Lyon prodigy Aouar, a gifted 21-year-old midfielder, has been on the books of Lyon since 2009. He broke into… June 3, 2020 In "Sports" Lyon coach Rudi Garcia has recently claimed that the French side is yet to receive any offers for a pair of their top stars. Lyon standouts Lyon did not have the most prolific 2019/20 campaign. Before COVID-19 brought football around Europe to a near standstill, Les Gones were sat 7th… June 17, 2020 In "Sports" Lyon sporting director Juninho had admitted that the club will “analyse” offers for star midfielder Houssem Aouar, amid rumours of interest from Manchester City. With David Silva set to leave the Etihad at the end of the season, Pep Guardiola may be looking to bolster his midfield. Phil Foden has… June 11, 2020 In "Sports"